parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Starter Ground Strap
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rubbing of the starter ground strap against the steel brake line can cause a hole to form, leading to a loss of brake fluid and brake pressure, which can result in a loss of braking ability and increase the risk of accidents.
